00:08.007 --> 00:11.876
Probably recover the
bull wheel, all the pulleys.

00:11.912 --> 00:14.212
A lot of lumber can be salvaged, too.

00:14.247 --> 00:18.416
Just enough to build a gallows.

00:20.554 --> 00:22.654
We gotta get another rig up and running.

00:22.689 --> 00:25.390
Start making calls.

00:25.425 --> 00:27.258
To who?

00:27.294 --> 00:29.160
We're not gonna get any
money out of the banks.

00:29.196 --> 00:31.062
Not after this.

00:31.098 --> 00:33.698
There's oil underneath this ground,

00:33.734 --> 00:35.266
and I intend to get it out,

00:35.302 --> 00:38.336
even if it means the three
of us digging our way to Hades

00:38.372 --> 00:39.571
with a pick and shovel

00:39.606 --> 00:41.106
Now figure it out!

00:41.141 --> 00:43.575
Well, we do have that
orphan eight sections

00:43.610 --> 00:44.864
up by the Midkiffs'.

00:44.867 --> 00:47.379
Are you suggesting we
sell to Percy Midkiff?

00:47.414 --> 00:48.713
Just those eight sections.

00:48.749 --> 00:50.825
That Bible-thumpin' son of a bitch?

00:50.828 --> 00:53.118
There ain't nothing up there
but brush and ladino bulls.

00:53.120 --> 00:55.387
You talk to me when you get serious.

01:01.094 --> 01:04.229
Selling land ain't exactly Daddy's way.

01:04.263 --> 01:05.915
I'll tell you one thing...

01:05.918 --> 01:08.299
We're about down to
selling that eight sections

01:08.301 --> 01:10.101
or having the bank sell
the whole ranch for us.

01:10.103 --> 01:11.669
You don't have to convince me.

01:13.774 --> 01:16.741
So, I guess you're just
expecting me to fix everything?

01:16.777 --> 01:18.710
As usual.

01:18.745 --> 01:21.146
I guess I better get to it, then.

01:24.818 --> 01:26.751
What about that other thing?

01:26.787 --> 01:28.953
It's being handled.

01:28.989 --> 01:30.455
By you or him?

01:30.490 --> 01:32.123
I got it covered. Don't you worry.

01:32.159 --> 01:34.959
Worrying is my job, little brother

01:40.767 --> 01:42.333
Morning, Mr. Sullivan.

01:42.369 --> 01:43.601
Hey, there, honey.

01:43.637 --> 01:45.670
You been out here a while.

01:45.705 --> 01:46.912
- Yep.
- Making sure those

01:46.915 --> 01:48.341
bandits don't come back?

01:48.375 --> 01:50.775
Well, if they do, they
sure gonna be sorry.

01:53.513 --> 01:55.613
But the river's that way.

01:55.649 --> 01:58.082
Isn't that where they'd
be approaching from?

01:58.118 --> 02:00.218
Why, I wish I would have
thought of that myself.

02:02.656 --> 02:04.789
That better?

02:06.560 --> 02:10.461
Now why don't you go on
inside and practice your piano?

02:10.497 --> 02:11.930
I know your granddaddy would love

02:11.965 --> 02:14.499
to hear you plink out
"Red River Valley" one day.

02:14.534 --> 02:16.668
That's boring.

02:16.703 --> 02:19.003
Well, then some other dulcet tune.

02:19.039 --> 02:21.039
Now go on. Git.

02:21.074 --> 02:22.774
Before I put you over my knee.

02:22.809 --> 02:26.478
I think my daddy might have
something to say about that.

