05:07.654 --> 05:09.454
Where do you think he is?

05:09.489 --> 05:11.990
I have no idea.

05:21.101 --> 05:22.500
Hmm.

05:27.274 --> 05:29.140
Okay, amigo.

05:29.175 --> 05:30.708
I'm letting you down.

05:41.788 --> 05:44.522
You destroyed my property.

05:48.061 --> 05:49.761
I wanna know why.

05:49.796 --> 05:53.364
Was it a reprisal for Armando?

06:00.573 --> 06:02.106
Suit yourself.

06:09.249 --> 06:10.748
From what everyone says,

06:10.784 --> 06:12.784
Cesar threw his lot
in with a rough crowd.

06:14.254 --> 06:15.887
You'd be surprised
how often these sorts,

06:15.922 --> 06:18.389
they disappear for a few
days, and then pop back up.

06:18.425 --> 06:20.792
Now maybe he's blowing
off steam in Mexico?

06:20.827 --> 06:25.396
Well, listen here, uh, here's a thought.

06:25.432 --> 06:27.966
The one oil rig the McCulloughs had up

06:28.001 --> 06:29.767
was attacked last night.

06:29.803 --> 06:32.603
I wonder if maybe Cesar was involved.

06:32.639 --> 06:34.978
Might explain his sudden disappearance.

06:36.187 --> 06:38.816
Well, that seems very unlikely to me.

06:38.847 --> 06:40.519
But you are right

06:40.535 --> 06:43.292
that was something wrong
happens around here,

06:43.320 --> 06:45.948
there's a tendency to blame
men who look like Cesar.

06:46.948 --> 06:48.352
Perhaps colonel McCullough

06:48.355 --> 06:50.154
was upset over the loss of his property

06:50.190 --> 06:52.457
and got the wrong idea
about my brother-in-law.

06:52.492 --> 06:56.260
Well, Eli is not exactly the
type to go off half-cocked.

06:56.296 --> 06:58.796
I'm sure you realize that
most of the voters in this town

06:58.832 --> 07:00.231
are Tejano?

07:00.266 --> 07:02.900
It would be so
unfortunate if word spread

07:02.936 --> 07:05.503
that you refused to
investigate the disappearance

07:05.538 --> 07:07.405
of Pedro García's son-in-law.

07:07.440 --> 07:09.640
I'd consider it a personal favor

07:09.676 --> 07:11.776
if you would speak to Eli McCullough.

07:27.694 --> 07:30.395
Where are your friends
crossing the river?

07:46.980 --> 07:48.646
Mm-hmm.

07:48.681 --> 07:50.148
What are they hitting next?

07:58.992 --> 08:00.358
What town are they coming from?

08:00.393 --> 08:01.526
Could I get a word?

08:12.372 --> 08:14.405
How far you planning on taking this?

08:14.441 --> 08:17.675
There are consequences
for a man's decisions...

08:17.710 --> 08:20.812
no matter what his last name.

08:20.847 --> 08:22.747
Aw, shit.

08:31.057 --> 08:32.957
Don't look at me.

08:34.928 --> 08:36.894
Keep an eye on this situation.

08:36.929 --> 08:38.895
- You got it, boss.
- Come on.

08:40.491 --> 08:42.366
You should just turn
him over to the sheriff.

08:42.368 --> 08:44.368
Be done with it.

08:44.404 --> 08:48.005
Well, we got to find out
what we're up against first.

08:48.041 --> 08:50.508
And the law is not
gonna help us do that.

08:50.543 --> 08:51.943
You beat a man long enough,

08:51.978 --> 08:53.978
he'll admit to crucifying the Savior.

08:56.112 --> 08:58.684
Probably best to let me do the talking.

09:06.826 --> 09:08.726
Ahh.

09:15.969 --> 09:18.136
So, what'd you do with the Mexican?

09:18.171 --> 09:21.472
Which Mexican are we talking about?

09:23.243 --> 09:24.609
Eli.

09:27.180 --> 09:30.414
I assume he got caught during
that unfortunate incident

09:30.450 --> 09:32.550
at your drilling rig.

09:32.585 --> 09:36.320
Those sons of bitches,
they got away scot-free.

09:36.356 --> 09:39.090
Is that right?

09:47.634 --> 09:51.569
Look, a man has a right
to protect his property.

09:51.604 --> 09:54.906
But I cannot have another incident.

09:54.941 --> 09:56.774
Am I right, Pete?

09:56.809 --> 09:59.143
Oh, I've been saying that for a while.

09:59.179 --> 10:01.245
Things need to simmer down.

10:01.281 --> 10:02.947
They sure as hell do.

10:04.859 --> 10:09.028
Pete, you heard anything
about this missing Cesar fella?

10:09.055 --> 10:12.390
Only that he travels
with a dangerous crowd.

10:18.865 --> 10:21.832
God damn it, Eli, you know
I wouldn't even be here

10:21.868 --> 10:23.534
if it wasn't for the election coming.

10:23.570 --> 10:25.536
- Mm-hmm.
- And the fact is,

10:25.572 --> 10:28.472
you can't win anything around
here without the Mexican vote.

10:28.508 --> 10:31.342
That means a lot of
cabrito come election day.

10:31.377 --> 10:33.511
Oh, well, believe me,
you have our support.

10:37.684 --> 10:39.951
You know, the Midkiffs
were generous enough

10:39.986 --> 10:41.352
to kick in $100.

10:43.489 --> 10:45.189
Well, now.

10:45.225 --> 10:46.991
Mark us down for $200.

10:47.026 --> 10:50.428
Well, that is exceedingly generous.

10:51.705 --> 10:53.197
Thank you.

